T1  - The Emperor Has No Clothes: Rewriting “Race in Organizations”
AU  - Nkomo, Stella M.
Y1  - 1992/07/01
PY  - 1992
DA  - 1992/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1992.4281987
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1992.4281987
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 487
EP  - 513
VL  - 17
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This article analyzes how race has been studied in organization scholarship and demonstrates how our approaches to the study at race reflect and reify particular historical and social meanings of race. It is argued that the production of knowledge about race must be understood within a racial ideology embedded in a Eurocentric view of the world. Finally, a ?re-vision? of the very concept of race and its historical and political meaning is suggested for rewriting ?race? as a necessary and productive analytical category for tpropheorizing about organizations.
AB  - This article analyzes how race has been studied in organization scholarship and demonstrates how our approaches to the study at race reflect and reify particular historical and social meanings of race. It is argued that the production of knowledge about race must be understood within a racial ideology embedded in a Eurocentric view of the world. Finally, a ?re-vision? of the very concept of race and its historical and political meaning is suggested for rewriting ?race? as a necessary and productive analytical category for tpropheorizing about organizations.
